ate of\nadaptive algorithms, which is $1-\\Theta(\\sqrt{1/k})$ due to Alaei (2014).\nSecond, turning to the IID setting, our framework allows us to numerically\nillustrate the tight guarantee (of adaptive algorithms) under any number $k$ of\nstarting units. Our guarantees for $k>1$ exceed the state-of-the-art.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 May 2022 00:28:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 30 Jan 2023 02:54:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-31"}
