{"id":"2205.00680","submitter":"Bas van den Heuvel","authors":"Bas van den Heuvel, Joseph W. N. Paulus, Daniele Nantes-Sobrinho,\n  Jorge A. P\\'erez","title":"Collapsing Non-determinism in Typed Lambda- and Pi-calculi","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.LO","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  We study non-determinism in functional and concurrent calculi with type\nsystems that control resources. We are motivated by the differences between\nso-called non-collapsing and collapsing non-deterministic choice. In\nnon-collapsing non-determinism, as induced by Curry-Howard correspondences, all\nbranches can reduce independently, ensuring confluence. The more common\ncollapsing non-determinism selects one branch and discards the rest, favoring\ncommitment over confluence. We investigate how to reconcile commitment with\ntype-based resource control. First, we introduce a $\\pi$-calculus with\ncollapsing non-deterministic choice, governed by session types; well-typed\nprocesses enjoy type preservation and deadlock-freedom. Second, we introduce a\nresource $\\lambda$-calculus with collapsing non-determinism, governed by\nintersection types; it enjoys subject reduction and expansion. Finally, we\nconnect the two typed non-deterministic calculi via a correct translation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 2 May 2022 06:41:07 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 May 2022 06:56:06 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 14 Mar 2023 09:12:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-15"}
